27/01/2005
WASHINGTON, United States -- State Department spokesman Richard Boucher has repeated Washington's support for UN-mediated talks between Macedonia and Greece aimed at resolving their ongoing dispute over Macedonia's constitutional name. In a statement for VoA's Macedonian-language programme Wednesday (26 January), Boucher reaffirmed that Washington would support any mutually acceptable solution resulting from the negotiations held under UN auspices. Boucher said the United States will continue to use the name Macedonia. (Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 27/01/05; Makfax, A1 TV - 25/01/05)
